WEBVTT

00:16:29.435 --> 00:16:31.110
Ellyn Shook: He was coming to work

00:16:31.134 --> 00:16:33.402
and nobody was talking
about what was happening.

00:16:33.426 --> 00:16:36.379
AdG: Ellyn is the Chief Leadership
and HR officer at Accenture.

00:16:36.403 --> 00:16:39.120
After talking with Darnel,
she decided to take action.

00:16:39.144 --> 00:16:43.470
ES: It was that moment
that "Building Bridges" was born.

00:16:43.494 --> 00:16:47.375
AdG: Ellyn, together with Julie Sweet,
Accenture's North America CEO,

00:16:47.399 --> 00:16:48.866
hosted a live Webcast.

00:16:49.355 --> 00:16:51.689
(Phone) Julie Sweet:
Today is a special town hall.

00:16:51.713 --> 00:16:56.760
It is about the difficult issues
that we are facing as a country,

00:16:56.784 --> 00:16:58.124
around race.

00:16:58.148 --> 00:17:01.847
AdG: They called it "Building Bridges,"
an open dialogue on diversity.